JOHANNESBURG – A  23-year-old male has been arrested following the death of a 21-year-old female student at Mangosuthu University of Technology's Lonsdale residence on Tuesday. According to the university, the former student was signed into the residence by another registered student where he allegedly shot the female student. “The University has learnt with shock of the sudden passing of a first year Quantity Surveying student. MUT warden at one of its outsourced residences, where the incident happened, reported that [she] was shot and killed by an ex-student of the University [Tuesday],” the university said in a statement. READ: Sandile Mantsoe found guilty of murder KZN spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane confirmed that the former student was arrested on the scene. “We can confirm the incident that took place on 1 May 2018 at about 11:00, at Lonsdale where a 21-year-old woman was fatally shot by a 23-year-old man. The suspect was arrested at the scene and the firearm was seized. The motive for the killing is unknown at this stage and he will appear in Durban Magistrates’ Court soon.” The suspect was found with an unlicensed firearm and ammunition. He has been charged with murder, possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition. eNCA